Using Entropy as a Library

* Using Entropy in a maven project

	Add a new dependency in your pom.xml and declare a new repository
	as Entropy is not uploaded into the central repository of maven:
	
	
---
<project>
  ...
  <dependencies>
    ...
    <dependency>
      <groupId>entropy</groupId>
      <artifactId>entropy</artifactId>
      <version>1.0</version>
      <scope>compile</scope>
    </dependency>
    ...
  </dependencies>
  ...
  <repositories>
    ...
    <repository>
      <id>entropy.releases</id>
      <name>Entropy releases</name>
      <url>http://entropy.gforge.inria.fr/repos/releases</url>
      <releases>
        <enabled>true</enabled>
      </releases>
      <snapshots>
        <enabled>false</enabled>
      </snapshots>
    </repository>
     ...
  </repositories>
  ...
</project>
---

